From: Vincent Fortier <th0ma7@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 31 May 2026
Subject: [PATCH] transcoding: stop stream cleanly after repeated encode failures

When a hardware encoder (e.g. h264_vaapi) enters a persistent error state,
avcodec_send_frame()/receive_packet() fail on every frame. tvh_context_decode()
remaps the resulting AVERROR(EIO)/EINVAL/EAGAIN/INVALIDDATA to 0, so the error
is silently swallowed and tvh_context_encode_frame() keeps being called on every
incoming packet with no recovery path. This was observed with h264_vaapi on Intel
Apollo Lake hardware emitting VA_STATUS_ERROR_ENCODING_ERROR (code 24) on a
1280x720@60fps input: tvheadend loops at ~2 errors/second while the mpegts input
queue grows unbounded ("too much queued input data (over 50MB)").

Fix by adding a consecutive encode-error counter (encode_errors) to TVHContext.
After TVH_MAX_ENCODE_ERRORS (3) consecutive failures, tvh_context_encode_frame()
returns AVERROR(ENODEV) -- a code that tvh_context_decode() does NOT remap to 0,
so it propagates up to tvh_transcoder_handle(), which calls tvh_stream_stop() and
tears the failing stream down cleanly via tvh_context_close(). Other streams of
the same subscription (e.g. audio) are unaffected. The counter is reset to zero
on any successful encode to avoid spurious stops on transient errors.

The teardown is intentionally left to the stop path: the encoder context is NOT
freed inside tvh_context_encode_frame(). An earlier revision freed self->oavctx
and set it to NULL, but because the EIO it returned was swallowed by
tvh_context_decode() the stream was never stopped, and the next packet re-entered
tvh_context_encode() where avcodec_is_open(self->oavctx) dereferenced the NULL
pointer and crashed (SIGSEGV in the tvh:sharer thread). As defence in depth,
tvh_context_encode() now also NULL-checks oavctx before avcodec_is_open().

Note: this addresses the infinite-loop / crash symptom. The root cause of the
persistent VA_STATUS_ERROR_ENCODING_ERROR is a separate issue in
libavcodec/hw_base_encode.c (see companion ffmpeg patches 0201/0202).

Link: https://github.com/tvheadend/tvheadend/issues/1833
Suggested-by: Claude Opus 4.8 (Anthropic AI <https://anthropic.com>)
Signed-off-by: Vincent Fortier <th0ma7@gmail.com>
---
 src/transcoding/transcode/context.c   | 28 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++-
 src/transcoding/transcode/internals.h |  3 +++
 2 files changed, 30 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- src/transcoding/transcode/internals.h.orig	2026-05-30 13:35:08.000000000 +0000
+++ src/transcoding/transcode/internals.h	2026-05-31 14:50:00.000000000 +0000
@@ -188,6 +188,9 @@
     // V4L2 is using AV_PKT_DATA_NEW_EXTRADATA so we need to change the conditions used for extradata
     // to signal that we set this variable to 1
     uint8_t use_pkt_data_new_extradata;
+    // consecutive encode-failure counter; once it reaches TVH_MAX_ENCODE_ERRORS
+    // the stream is torn down cleanly instead of looping forever (or crashing).
+    int encode_errors;
 };
 
 int
--- src/transcoding/transcode/context.c.orig	2026-05-30 13:35:08.000000000 +0000
+++ src/transcoding/transcode/context.c	2026-05-31 14:50:00.000000000 +0000
@@ -733,6 +733,9 @@
 }
 
 
+// Number of consecutive encode failures tolerated before the stream is stopped.
+#define TVH_MAX_ENCODE_ERRORS 3
+
 static int
 tvh_context_encode_frame(TVHContext *self, AVFrame *avframe)
 {
@@ -750,6 +753,29 @@
     }
     if ((ret = (ret == AVERROR_EOF) ? 0 : ret)) {
         av_frame_unref(avframe);
+        // Track consecutive encode failures. A hardware encoder (e.g. h264_vaapi)
+        // can enter a persistent error state and return -EIO on every frame; without
+        // a recovery path tvheadend would loop forever calling this on each input
+        // packet. avframe is NULL only during flush, which must not count as an error.
+        if (avframe) {
+            self->encode_errors++;
+            tvh_context_log(self, LOG_WARNING,
+                "encode error %d/%d", self->encode_errors, TVH_MAX_ENCODE_ERRORS);
+            if (self->encode_errors >= TVH_MAX_ENCODE_ERRORS) {
+                tvh_context_log(self, LOG_ERR,
+                    "too many consecutive encode errors, stopping stream");
+                self->encode_errors = 0;
+                // Return a fatal error that tvh_context_decode() does NOT remap to 0
+                // (unlike EAGAIN/EINVAL/EIO/INVALIDDATA). It then propagates up to
+                // tvh_transcoder_handle(), which calls tvh_stream_stop() to tear the
+                // stream down cleanly via tvh_context_close(). Do not free oavctx here:
+                // teardown is the stop path's responsibility, and freeing it would let
+                // a later packet re-enter tvh_context_encode() with oavctx == NULL.
+                ret = AVERROR(ENODEV);
+            }
+        }
+    } else {
+        self->encode_errors = 0;
     }
     return ret;
 }
@@ -781,7 +807,9 @@
 {
     int ret = 0;
 
-    if (!avcodec_is_open(self->oavctx)) {
+    // Guard against a NULL encoder context: avcodec_is_open() dereferences its
+    // argument, so a missing oavctx would otherwise segfault here.
+    if (!self->oavctx || !avcodec_is_open(self->oavctx)) {
         ret = tvh_context_open_encoder(self);
     }
     if (!ret && !(ret = tvh_context_push_frame(self, avframe))) {
